This paper deals with the traveling salesman problem with neighborhoods (TSPN) in the plane, which involves finding a tour that visits a set of geometric objects (in this case, disks) with certain constraints. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also presents a constant-ratio approximation algorithm, which involves analyzing the structure of the problem and designing efficient algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) likely categories as well. The paper also involves analyzing the performance of the algorithm and proving theoretical guarantees, which falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
